Code of Conduct
As contributors and maintainers of the VK programming language, we pledge to foster an open and welcoming environment for everyone, regardless of age, body size, disability, ethnicity, gender identity and expression, level of experience, nationality, personal appearance, race, religion, or sexual identity and orientation.

Our Standards
Examples of behavior that contributes to creating a positive environment include:

Being respectful and considerate of others
Being open to constructive criticism and feedback
Showing empathy and kindness towards fellow contributors
Welcoming newcomers and helping them get involved in the community
Respecting diverse viewpoints and experiences
Examples of unacceptable behavior include:

Harassment, intimidation, or discrimination of any form
Offensive, derogatory, or disrespectful comments or language
Personal attacks, insults, or trolling
Disruptive behavior or spamming
Any other conduct that violates the principles of a safe and inclusive community
Our Responsibilities
Project maintainers are responsible for clarifying the standards of acceptable behavior and are expected to take appropriate and fair corrective action in response to any instances of unacceptable behavior.

Enforcement
Instances of abusive, harassing, or otherwise unacceptable behavior may be reported by contacting the project team at contact@beasova.xyz All complaints will be reviewed and investigated promptly and fairly.

Project maintainers have the right and responsibility to remove, edit, or reject comments, commits, code, wiki edits, issues, and other contributions that are not aligned with this Code of Conduct, or to ban temporarily or permanently any contributor for behaviors that they deem inappropriate, threatening, offensive, or harmful.

Scope
This Code of Conduct applies to all contributors, both online and offline, as well as to all project-related spaces and activities, including but not limited to project repositories, forums, mailing lists, chat rooms, and events.

Acknowledgment
This Code of Conduct is adapted from the Contributor Covenant, version 2.0, available at https://www.contributor-covenant.org/version/2/0/code_of_conduct.html.

Contact
If you have any questions or concerns about this Code of Conduct, please contact the project team at contact@beasova.xyz

Enforcement
Instances of abusive, harassing, or otherwise unacceptable behavior may be reported to the project team at contact@beasova.xyz  All complaints will be reviewed and investigated promptly and fairly. All project maintainers are obligated to respect the privacy and security of the reporter of any incident.

Attribution
This Code of Conduct is adapted from the Contributor Covenant, version 2.0, available at https://www.contributor-covenant.org/version/2/0/code_of_conduct.html.
